===Etymology===
From the [[Hindi]] ''champo'', the [[imperative]] form of the verb ''champna'', meaning "to press or knead the muscles," i.e., to [[massage]].

===Noun===
# A traditional [[Indian]] and [[Persian]] body [[massage]] given after pouring [[warm]] [[water]] over the body and rubbing it with [[extract]]s from [[herb]]s.
# A [[commercial]] [[liquid]] [[soap]] product for [[wash]]ing [[hair]] or other fibres, such as [[carpet]]s.

